## WDD CLI Commands
You have access to the `wdd` CLI. Use it actively:

### Before starting work
Run `wdd session` to get full project context.

### When writing tests for a new Ward
Run `wdd ward status <id> red` after writing test files.

### When tests are approved and you start implementing
Run `wdd ward status <id> gold` before writing implementation.

### When implementation is done and all tests pass
Report to human. Do NOT run `wdd complete` — that's a human action.

### To check project health
Run `wdd validate` before reporting completion.

### To regenerate progress
Run `wdd progress` after any ward status change.

### To search for past decisions
Run `wdd search "<query>"` or `wdd search --tag "<tag>"` when you need context about previous architectural decisions.
